 to the settled and closed practices that structure our political world and to provide a hopeful vision of what it means to be politically progressive today.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aDemocracyxPhilosophy. 0aPolitical participationxSocial aspects. 0aPolitical sociology. 0aProtest movements. 4aPhilosophy : Critical Theory. 4aPolitics and Law : Democracy. 4aPolitics and Law : Political Theory. 4aPolitics and Law : Politics. 4aSociology : Social Problems. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / History & Theory.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143846783240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438467832423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438467832/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles